When synthesizing this literature, emphasize the behavioral evidence for
differential treatment of income versus windfall/wealth. Connect warm glow
findings to questions about intrinsic versus instrumental motivations for
meeting giving norms. Use pledge effectiveness research to evaluate claims
about income-based commitments like the 10% pledge. Consider how social
norm research illuminates the feasibility of shifting from income-based to
asset-based giving norms.

KEY_POSITIONS:
- Warm glow / impure altruism: 6 papers - Giving motivated by intrinsic satisfaction alongside altruistic concern
- Social norms influence: 5 papers - Both descriptive and injunctive norms shape donation behavior
- Income/wealth effects: 4 papers - Differential responses to earned income, windfall income, and wealth
- Pledge effectiveness: 3 papers - Mixed evidence on commitment mechanisms for sustained giving
